gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 115, 76ers 102
gameRecap.excerpt: The Suns defeated the 76ers, 115-102 as they improved to 40-29 on the year. Grayson Allen led the Suns with 32 points (9-15 3PT) and five assists as Kevin Durant (22 points, eight rebounds) and Devin Booker (18 points, nine rebounds, 11 assists) added 40 points. Kelly Oubre Jr. led Philadelphia with 18 points while KJ Martin added 11 points and 13 rebounds. The 76ers moved to 38-31.
